SIMPLE: gladsome
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gladsome
<hw>Glad"some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pleased;
joyful; cheerful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Causing joy, pleasure, or cheerfulness; having the
appearance of gayety; pleasing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of opening heaven they sung, and <qex>gladsome</qex> day.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Glad"some*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Glad"some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hours of perfect <qex>gladsomeness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>gladsomeness</ent>⟦br⟧
